guy who was nailed to a tree for saying it would be good to<br>
be nice to people for a change.<br>
<br>
If there was no resurrection, then Jesus was, at best, just<br>
another prophet, another also-ran among claims of people <br>
being the messiah, one amongst the ranks who still grow<br>
in the 21st century. <br>
<br>
If Christ be not raised, we are among men most miserable,<br>
as the apostle Paul tells it.<br>
<br>
The good news is the price paid, redemption purchased,<br>
salvation given.  Jesus crucified, died, buried, resurrected,<br>
ascended, and returning a time yet to come. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naglfarir>naglfarir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#B87333>(10/28/03 11:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=51.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Christology- Neccesary ressurection.</span><hr size=1>  Yes you are right on most points. However but what if we keep all the rest of the gospel and pull out the resurrection.<br>
